  "prompt": "Was Charlie Chaplin a Gypsy?",
  "response": "Charlie Chaplin was not of Gypsy descent, though there has been some speculation and rumors about his heritage over the years. Chaplin himself mentioned in his autobiography that he believed there might be some Romani ancestry on his mother's side, but this was never confirmed. His father, Charles Chaplin Sr., was English, and his mother, Hannah Chaplin, whose stage name was Lily Harley, was also of English descent. Despite the uncertainty, Chaplin embraced the idea with curiosity, reflecting the broader themes of identity and belonging that often appeared in his work.",
